snippet.textDisplay: the way I read the video: everybody has some form of trauma. whether it's the rabbit getting struck in the face or the kid watching his parents fight, things affect people in different ways. this seems reinforced by the wireframe graphics which really resemble neural pathways. so when the rabbit gets scratched, the traumatic event creates a new set of neural pathways. it also illustrates how people react differently to trauma: the bunny becomes hardened and tough, the kid becomes reclusive and scared. the celestial/spiritual side of it seems to be another realm that is higher; julian seems to think that despite the traumas that happen on earth, things will always be better in the end
